<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2010-08-02</DATELINE><TITLE>Advanced Diagnostic Approaches and Current Management of Proventricular Dilatation Disease</TITLE><BODY>Proventricular dilatation disease (PDD) is a fatal inflammatory disease that affects mainly, but not exclusively, psittacine birds (Order: Psittaciformes). PDD has long been suspected to be a viral disease, but its causative agent, a novel Bornavirus, was only identified in 2008.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>